A second case of Covid-19 has been confirmed. This time it's a 39-year-old who has been in direct contact with the first case from KwaZulu-Natal. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The second case of COVID-19 has been confirmed in South Africa. According to the Health Department, a 39-year-old woman was in direct contact with the first known case of a man in KwaZulu-Natal. The woman was part of a group of 10 that had travelled to Italy. The first patient and his wife were also part of the group. WATCH:Â Doctor of SA's first coronavirus patient speaks The Ministry has moved to assure the public that the 10 people who travelled on the same flight to Italy are all being tested. It's currently waiting on those results.